msgid "You need two laptops in order to use this activity."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/distance.rst:27
# 5d03bbb05f464f35a871840234b850a8
msgid "Steps"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/distance.rst:29
# 1a79a38b1d3d4ff988836f2e171b6151
msgid "Launch the Distance activity on one of the computers by clicking on the icon in the Home view."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/distance.rst:31
# 8dd77eac97ba4e0ab647120f4ef391e3
msgid "Share the activity from the Share icon on the activity toolbar (or send an invitation to the another computer)."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/distance.rst:33
# 5aee42f2732d472882352c8f92991ad9
msgid "Launch the Distance activity on the second computer by clicking on the icon in the Neighborhood view (or Invitation icon)."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/distance.rst:35
# c27d81d894f74ea08cbbd38ad4e3d87d
msgid "Click on the \"Begin Measuring Distance\" button found near the top of the activity view on both computers."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/distance.rst:37
# 348f373a1a3b4a9c82802baec53db0cc
msgid "The first computer will send an audio pulse; the second computer will respond with an audio pulse of its own; then both computers will calculate and display the distance between them (by default, the measurement is displayed in meters)."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/distance.rst:39
# 90972c94e1f745daae968a06ac5646fa
msgid "This process (Step 5) will repeat until you click on the \"Stop Measuring Distance\" button or you exit the activity."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/distance.rst:42
# 9d39f709085943fcb1818d185c018132
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/distance.rst:44
# 0338a04ae1314a349a53f107f643c99d
msgid "Try not to move the laptops while a measurement is taking place as it will result in a inaccurate measurement. You can move them between consecutive measurements."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/distance.rst:46
# d99a0b0c910c4976821af9fea81eafd8
msgid "If the \"Begin Measuring Distance\" button does not activate, try relaunching the Distance activity again on the second laptop from the Neighborhood view."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/distance.rst:50
# 55516914d49b4e3aa75c4983a809cb1a
msgid "Atmospheric conditions can impact the accuracy of the measurement; you can override the default settings by using the Atmosphere toolbar."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/distance.rst:54
# 92cc81461de34206a3e7cfca03172226
msgid "The units of measure can be changed by choosing a unit from the combo box (meters, centimeters, inches, feet, yards, or custom units) on the Customize toolbar. If you chose \"custom units\", the current distance between the two laptops will be used as a metric. For example, you could measure the height of a student, Pedro, and then select that distance to define a new unit of measure, the \"Pedro\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/distance.rst:58
# ba49c24839f84c7f89e14f71b8f0738b
msgid "The Copy button found on the Edit toolbar can be used to copy measurements to the toolbar."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/distance.rst:60
# 823807fdaead45b9b8659dcdbbe62ff1
msgid "The Paste button found on the Edit toolbar can be used to paste a new measurement unit into the activity. The scale of the measurement units should be specified in terms of meters, e.g., 39.37 for specifying inches."
msgstr ""

